sourcesContent:
export const portfolioData = [
  {
    id: 1,
    name: 'moms-burgers.herokuapp.com',
    languages: ['react', 'javascript', 'css'],
    languagesIcons: ['fab fa-js', 'fab fa-react', 'fab fa-sass'],
    source: 'https://github.com/swann-martin/moms-burgers',
    info: 'Just a simple example of a burger shop build for fun using react with hooks for the cart. ',
    picture: './media/project1.png',
  },
  {
    id: 2,
    name: 'swann-meteo.surge.sh',
    languages: ['javascript', 'react'],
    languagesIcons: ['fab fa-js', 'fab fa-react'],
    source: 'https://github.com/swann-martin/react-weather-app',
    info: 'This website was made in a day at then ending of a training on react. The aim was to make it possible for the user to search for the weather in his/her city. I used axios to fetch open weather api, react, sass, font-awsome and surge to deploy.',
    picture: './media/project2.png',
  },
  {
    id: 3,
    name: 'jummmp créé ton cv',
    languages: ['javascript', 'php', 'css', 'symfony'],
    languagesIcons: [
      'fab fa-js',
      'fab fa-php',
      'fab fa-css3-alt',
      'fab fa-symfony',
    ],
    source: 'https://github.com/swann-martin/archive_jummmp',
    info: 'Web application delivered during the evaluation for the CNCP certification Web Integration Techniques & Web Development Techniques. Directed by Swann Martin, Michael Krysztofiak & Thomas Barnabé.',
    picture: './media/project3.png',
  },
  {
    id: 4,
    name: 'react-sofa.herokuapp.com',
    languages: ['javascript', 'react'],
    languagesIcons: ['fab fa-js', 'fab fa-react'],
    source: 'https://github.com/swann-martin/react-leSofa',
    info: 'The aim was to recreate a simple website using ReactJS with sass, react-router-dom and react-router. It is a mock website for a fake company very interested in sofas.',
    picture: './media/project4.png',
  },
  {
    id: 5,
    name: 'react-quiz',
    languages: ['typescript', 'css'],
    languagesIcons: ['fab fa-js', 'fab fa-css3-alt'],
    source: 'https://github.com/swann-martin/react-quiz',
    info: 'This project was made following a YouTube tutorial to learn React.js and TypeScript and material ui. Trivia API was used to generate the questions.',
    picture: './media/project5.png',
  },
  {
    id: 6,
    name: 'animated portfolio project',
    languages: ['javascript', 'react', 'sass'],
    languagesIcons: ['fab fa-js', 'fab fa-react', 'fab fa-sass'],
    source: 'https://github.com/swann-martin/react-tuto2',
    info: ' This project was made following a Youtube tutorial to learn React.js. It was made with React.js and Sass. ',
    picture: './media/project6.png',
  },
  {
    id: 7,
    name: 'WashAtHome',
    languages: ['javascript', 'react', 'sass'],
    languagesIcons: ['fab fa-js', 'fab fa-react', 'fab fa-sass'],
    source: 'https://github.com/swann-martin/washathome',
    info: " This project was in group as an end of training project for my specialization in React.js with O'Clock School. It was made using Reactjs, Redux, Sass, react-leaflet, nodejs . ",
    picture: './media/project7.png',
  },
];
